name: The Drunken Ship
review_text:
Questo pub a Campo de' Fiori è un piccolo gioiello nel cuore di Roma, perfetto sia per un drink all'interno sia per un momento di relax all'esterno, sorseggiando una birra con qualche snack. Qui si possono seguire partite di calcio e altri sport, incontrando un pubblico internazionale, composto da inglesi, americani, italiani e studenti di passaggio.

In una città ricca di locali, questo pub si distingue per l’atmosfera vivace e giovanile e per l'ottima selezione di birre alla spina, sempre fresche e di qualità. È il luogo ideale per chi cerca un buon hamburger e una birra ben spillata, in un contesto allegro e senza pretese.

The decor and ambience is very American. You can even see a big American flag 🇺🇸 as part of the decor. Basically you will feel as if you are in an American sports bar.
Our waitress was Sep. I hope 🤞 not mistake on her name.  She was very attentive and provided a great service.
We enjoyed our coffee  and the bar.
Definitely recommend this place.   Thanks.

name: The Drunken Ship
review_text: Esperienza pessima. Io, una mia amica e il mio ragazzo arriviamo intorno alle 22, tavoli esterni quasi tutti vuoti, prima di noi entra un gruppo di turisti, chiediamo alla “security” di poterci sedere ma ci dicono che dentro è tutto prenotato, rispondiamo che vanno benissimo i tavoli fuori, ci rispondono che non sanno dove mettere il gruppo appena entrato e “probabilmente” è tutto già preso, intanto continuano a far entrare turisti. Praticamente entrano tutti tranne noi. Dopo 2/3 ore riproviamo ad entrare perché la mia amica voleva prendere da bere al volo al banco e la “security” ci risponde che non è serata. Il tutto con un locale pieno solo di turisti in cui continuava ad entrare ed uscire gente. Sinceramente in un locale che nel menù promuove la diversità con agevolazioni agli studenti internazionali dispiace molto l’incoerenza perché far entrare solo turisti sembra ipocrisia.
review_text_translated: Bad experience.I, a friend of mine and my boyfriend we arrive around 10 pm, almost all empty external tables, before us a group of tourists enters, we ask the "Security" to be able to sit but they tell us that everything is booked inside, we reply that they are fineThe tables outside, they reply that they do not know where to put the group just entered and "probably" is everything already taken, meanwhile they continue to bring tourists into tourists.They practically all enter except us.After 2/3 hours we try to enter because my friend wanted to take to drink on the bench and the "Security" replies that it is not an evening.All with a place full of tourists only in which people continued to enter and exit.Honestly, in a place that in the menu promotes diversity with facilitations to international students, it is very sorry for inconsistency because making tourists only seem hypocrisy.

review_text: AVOID this establishment. We were unexpectedly ejected without justification, despite having ordered drinks. After waiting outside for approximately 30 minutes, with assurances of a table from several servers, we were finally seated. However, within 4-5 minutes of sitting and ordering drinks, a group of girls arrived, and the manager promptly removed our table settings and forced us to leave. Despite having already paid for our drinks, the manager was insistent on us leaving. While the staff were extremely courteous throughout the ordeal, the manager's actions were highly inappropriate. I advise against supporting such practices; it's simply unacceptable.

name: The Drunken Ship
review_text: YOU REALLY GOT ME ! on Monday, Sept 24th my wife and I were in the middle of a private guided tour of ancient sites in Rome, Italy...the Colosseum, Vatican City, Sistine Chapel and St Peter's Basilica. Valeria our private tour guide brought us to a fabulous bakery / cafe to grab some lunch after our incredible tour of the Colosseum. When I get my hands on a delectable panino ( flatbread ) sandwich I need to pair it with a great tastin' beer. AND I DID ! Right next door was this pub and it served a good selection of Belgian beers and IPA's. YES PLEASE ! I couldn't believe my luck finding a good beer joint like this in Italy. I had been drinking very average Italian beers and unknown imported beers since we landed in Italy a few days ago. If I couldn't get hazy IPA's ( there were none ) then it had to be Belgian beers. A cool barman named Guglielmo helped me at the bar....he gave me a sample of a couple of beers and the St Benoit "Supreme" Belgian Strong Ale - 6.8% abv won the day. AND WHAT A GREAT BEER ! Well let me tell this excellent tasting beer paired perfectly with my scrumptious panino sandwich. SO GOOD ! In fact being starved of great tastin' beers I convinced my wife we needed to come back here. We got a taxi back to Campo de' Fiori the next day and did it all again. Panino sandwiches and a great tastin' Belgian beer for me. Oh and Guglielmo is a drummer in a local band. CAN'T BE BEATEN !

name: The Drunken Ship
review_text:
I recently visited The Drunken Ship, a bar that caters to a young crowd, primarily from the United States. The atmosphere of the bar was nice, with a lively and energetic vibe. One of the standout features of the bar was the beer pong table in the back, which added to the fun and social atmosphere of the place.

However, my experience at The Drunken Ship was slightly dampened by the state of the bathroom. There was only one stall for both men and women, which led to long lines and wait times. To make matters worse, the stall lacked basic amenities such as toilet paper and soap, which made for an uncomfortable and unsanitary experience.

Overall, while The Drunken Ship has some great features, such as its fun and lively atmosphere and beer pong table, the state of the bathroom is a significant downside. I hope that the management takes steps to address this issue so that patrons can have a more comfortable and enjoyable experience at the bar.

name: The Drunken Ship
review_text:
I had a great time here.
I found the staff to be friendly and attentive enough. The vibe (music and decor) is clearly geared towards the college-dive crowd.. but Im totally fine with that.
The one bathroom's cleanliness needs more attention. (More for the female patrons' sake).
It was very empty when I went (during the middle of the day of a windy work week), which worked out great for my group and I...until a strong gust of wind knocked over a couple of the giant outdoor dining umbrellas and sent the American flag on a collision course w/the back of my head (we were drunk enough to find all that hilarious at the time).

Drinks and food were very decently priced, in my opinion (Salmon & avocado club sandwich for €10!! Hell yea!)
They even gave us 4 free shots.
I'm definitely coming back next time I'm in Rome.

name: The Drunken Ship
review_text: The bar has a nice location and some of the staff are nice. However, I cannot give more than a star because, besides being tremendously overpriced and playing unnecessarily loud music, one of the bartenders literally bullied me, without any exaggeration. He aggressively shouted senseless things at me every time he saw me in a disrespectfully and mockingly loud voice. When he shouted at me for the umpteenth time and I ignored him, he moved towards me and brazenly patted me on the back. I really wonder where the head of the person who hired him was at when they did. The degree of indolence to his aggressiveness and rudeness of the other bartenders cannot be overstated. Not going back to this bar ever again.

review_text: Sono dei ladri. Il ragazzo che lavora li è un gran cafone.. Ho chiesto due spritz portati in un bicchiere dalla capienza normale, al secondo giro ci hanno portato due spritz al bicchiere Dell amaro per un costo di 32 euro. Zero stuzzichini e tanta maleducazione e strafottenza.. Il barista "veterano", alla mia lamentela ha risposto di scrivere una recensione negativa. Io il secondo spritz l ho pagato ma l ho buttato.. Dovremmo farlo tutti. La signora(inglese) accanto a me ha pagato per due coca cola la bellezza di 15 euro.il barista andrebbe licenziato! Che vergogna!
review_text_translated: They are thieves.The guy who works is a great peasant .. I asked for two spritz brought to a glass with a normal capacity, on the second lap they brought us two spritz to the glass of the bitterness for a cost of 32 euros.Zero snacks and lots of rudeness and arrogance .. The "veteran" bartender, to my complaint he replied to write a negative review.I paid the second spritz but I threw it .. we should all do it.The (English) lady next to me paid for two coca cola the beauty of 15 euros. The bartender should be fired!What a shame!

name: The Drunken Ship
review_text: On our last night in Rome, all my friends and I wanted to do was to go to our favorite bar, Drunken Ship. When we got there some bald douché bag with a velvet rope refused to let us in. With no good reason I must add. Little do they know, my friends and I were planning on spending the rest of our money that night. Their loss I guess, because we just took our business to Scholars. I highly recommend going there instead. All the Drunken Ship cares about is getting American girls drunk and taking advantage of them. Can’t believe five Americans willing to spend a check at an American bar got denied. Very disappointing.

Locale molto frequentato da stranieri e locali da tutto il mondo .
Anche lo staff della sicurezza è attento al passaggio dei clienti .

An American style local in Piazza Campo de Fiori, where you can taste different qualities of craft beers and cocktails prepared with sympathy and attention from the barman.The staff in the room very kind and friendly.
Local very popular with foreigners and clubs from all over the world.
The security staff is also attentive to the passage of customers.

review_text_translated: The waiter told me "vafanculo" and pushed me out immediately after I commanded a drink only because he did another drink in his hand.I will never return to this place after the tratancent who made me.Good education is always welcome !!

name: The Drunken Ship
review_text:
Tourist trap. Music is tremendously loud and annoying, food was late and horribly prepared. Pasta was nuked in the microwave- not sure how you could mess up pesto pasta. Perhaps if you’re drunk enough, you’ll enjoy the food. I get that it’s bar food- but even bar food should be prepared well and be edible.
It most definitely is a drunken ship- it put our family on the poop deck and had us walk the plank.

review_text: Non lo consiglio per niente, il buttafuori maleducato mentre rientravo al locale mi ha spinto in modo molto aggressivo, senza una giusta motivazione e chiesto di andarmene. Dopo avere spiegato a lui che ero un cliente e che i miei amici erano seduti affianco all’ingresso, egli intelligentemente ha iniziato a minacciarmi dicendo “se non ti piace il posto puoi andartene, cammina”. Ho detto a questo che non sono i modi di trattare un cliente e io e i miei amici abbiamo cambiato locale. Evitate questo posto.
review_text_translated: I do not recommend it at all, the rude bob as I returned to the restaurant pushed me very aggressively, without a right motivation and asked to leave.After explaining to him that I was a client and that my friends were sitting next to the entrance, he intelligently started threatening me by saying "if you don't like the place you can leave, walk".I told this that they are not the ways of treating a customer and my friends and I changed local.Avoid this place.

name: The Drunken Ship
review_text: Siamo arrivati, abbiamo aspettato un'ora pazientemente che si liberasse il tavolo da beer pong, appena disponibile anche altri ragazzi volevano giocare e ci siamo messi d'accordo per fare un partita insieme con il permesso del personale (buttafuori e cameriere). All'improvviso arriva il propietario e ci dice che non possono giocare in più di due contro due e senza spettatori, quando il gruppo che ci ha preceduto era in numero notevolmente superiore. Ci siamo rimasti malissimo, non è questo il modo di trattare dei clienti senza motivo: nessuna aveva ancora bevuto niente e il contesto della partita era amichevole, non c'erano problemi di sorta. Altra nota negativa pare che avessero una preferenza di servizio verso gli studenti stranieri a cui si dedicavano continuamente , mentre noi abbiamo solo aspettato e ce ne siamo andati a mani vuote. Propietario, se stai leggendo sappi che ci hai rovinato la serata di Halloween, se non volevi che stessimo nel tuo locale avresti dovuto avere le palle di farci uscire prima anziché perdere solo tempo.
review_text_translated: We arrived, we waited patiently that the Beer Pong table would get rid of, just available other guys also wanted to play and we agreed to take a game together with the staff permission (bouncer and waitresses).Suddenly the proportion arrives and tells us that they cannot play in more than two against two and without spectators, when the group that preceded us was considerably higher.We remained very bad, this is not the way of dealing with customers without reason: none had still drunk anything and the context of the game was friendly, there were no problems whatsoever.Another negative note seems that they had a service preference for foreign students to whom they continually dedicated themselves, while we only expected and we went empty hands.Propperitaria, if you are reading you know that you ruined us the Halloween evening, if you didn't want me to have been in your place you would have had to have the balls to let us out first instead of wasting only time.

review_text: Esperienza terribile, da non ripetere e non consigliare. Abbiamo chiesto due lattine di bibite, ce le hanno portate appiccicose nella loro confezione e calde. I bicchieri pieni di ghiaccio erano sporchi....avrebbero dovuto avvertirci del fatto che non fossero fresche, perché io non amo bere bevande con l aggiunta di ghiaccio. Il prezzo esagerato, 4 euro a lattina. Malauguratamente ho utilizzato i servizi igienici e purtroppo mi chiedo come facciano a rimanere aperti, in quanto non superavano di certo nessun tipo di controllo igienico sanitario, puzza e sporcizia orrendi, una latrina per ambo i sensi, in condizioni davvero pietose. Consiglio di rivedere i canoni di pulizia....così non si può fare nulla, men che meno pub/bar/ristorazione.
review_text_translated: Terrible experience, not to be repeated and not recommend.We asked for two cans of drinks, they brought them sticky in their package and hot.The glasses full of ice were dirty .... they should have warned us that they were not fresh, because I don't like drinking drinks with the addition of ice.The exaggerated price, 4 euros per can.Unfortunately I used the toilets and unfortunately I wonder how they remain open, as they certainly did not exceed any kind of sanitary control, stenching and dirt, a latrine for both senses, in really pitiful conditions.I recommend reviewing the cleaning fees .... so nothing can be done, less than less pub/bar/catering.

name: The Drunken Ship
review_text:
Student bar for American kids. Probably be fun for American 18/19 year olds looking to get drunk, hook up and experience nothing about Italy. That's not necessarily a a criticism. Just my personal opinion.

The northern Irish barman is very nice the Italian guy was not and was just arrogant after I made my orders in Italian, presumably because he realised I wasn't gonna tip him on top of the ludicrously overpriced, supermarket standard beer he served me.

However the ridiculous US flags draped over every surface and the beer pong table just give it a cheap "pub crawl" look.

Used to be better many years back, and it really needs a lick of paint.

Ma anche burger+beer 10€

Perfect for an afternoon of relaxation, external tables directly on Campo dei Fiori.

name: The Drunken Ship
review_text: Il miglior posto se ti piace bere buona birra e conoscere gente nuova e simpatica. Ciliegina sulla torta, il personale disponibile e cortese; non capita ovunque di trovare alti livelli di competenza come al Drunken Ship. Ideale sia all'ora di pranzo, quando si può anche curiosare nel mercato giornaliero di Campo de' Fiori, sia di sera quando si popola di giovani stranieri e non. Un mix ideale che promette una serata all'insegna del divertimento.
review_text_translated: The best place if you like to drink good beer and meet new and nice people.Icing on the cake, helpful and courteous staff;It does not happen everywhere to find high levels of competence such as at the Drunken Ship.Ideal both at lunchtime, when you can also browse the daily market of Campo de 'Fiori, and in the evening when it is populated by young and non -foreigners.An ideal mix that promises an evening of fun.

review_text: Just know that this place is considered "the american bar" so if you are ok with that in Italy, then have a blast! name: The Drunken Ship
review_text:
Perfect spot for me to hang out...20 years ago :) Packed to the rafters with American college kids lucky enough to find themselves in Rome. The first question you'll get when you order a beer is "Are you a student?" (Well..if you aren't pushing 40 like me). The next question is "Is this for beer pong?" Presumably this is for a discount...not to deny service.

This would have been right up my alley a few years ago...but you'll have to fight your way through a crowd packt like sardines in a crushed tin box to get a drink. Grab a couple anyway, even if you are youth-challenged like myself. Then move on to the more relaxed bars that line Campo De Fiori. Or if you've still got the urge to play beer pong...well you probably didn't make it past the first sentence of my review. Enjoy the student discounts and the fact that you can deal with the hangover better than your future self will!

review_text: The Drunken Ship is one of the worst bars in Rome. Immediately after walking in and ordering a drink the bartender made racist remarks towards my friend by saying “you look Asian or wait maybe Egyptian”. These remarks are completely unacceptable. We then went to go play a game of beer pong and my friend missed a shot and her partner wrapped his arm around my friend and covered her mouth. The bouncer saw this happen and did absolutely nothing. He blamed the incident on us and said that is was our fault we wanted to play. If you are in this area do not go to this bar, plenty of other bars where you get treated with respect near by.

name: The Drunken Ship
review_text: My time at the drunken ship was the worst bar experience I have ever had, hands down. It started off by ordering a drink and the bar tender asking if I was Asian (I am not) and pulling the corner of his eyes so to make the squinty..... Then we were invited to play beer pong with a group of guys, I missed one shot and my partner swiftly put his and over my mouth and nose and pushed me. The bouncer did nothing (even though he saw the whole thing) until myself, and my friend asked him to kick him out. The bouncer replied to me saying “it was my fault because I was playing beer pong”. The guy was eventually escorted out. My friend and I left to see him fighting his way to get back in, so I looked at the door man and said don’t let him back in and got a “calm down” in reply. There are plenty of fun bars around the area DO NOT GO TO THE DRUNKEN SHIP.

name: The Drunken Ship
review_text:
Positives:
The staff are very friendly.
Very tourist friendly for English speakers.
Student discounts are amazing!
The location is superb and within walking distance of a few other pubs.

Drawbacks:
The bathroom is unfortunately the most disgusting ones I have ever seen.

In short, I would definitely recommend this place to any young student tourist looking for a place to get cheap drinks while out on the town.
